        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001270_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><date when="1858-03-06">6 March 1858</date></dateline>
<lb/><space extent="4" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="town">Birkenhead</settlement></placeName> 
<lb/><persName>Bevan Braithwaite<choice><abbr>Esq</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></persName>
<lb/><salute>My Dear Friend,</salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p rend="right">I enclose a note
<lb/>from <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName> and
<lb/>an answer which if
<lb/>you see no objection
<lb/>to I shall trouble you
<lb/>to forward. I also send
<lb/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> John Moffat</persName>'s
<lb/>letter in reference to it
<lb/>if you think it better not
<lb/>to send the letter burn it

	<pb facs="liv_001270_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>I have kept no copy</p>
<lb/><p><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">s</hi> Wilbraham Taylor</persName>
<lb/>went to <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName>
<lb/>about the other or pecuniary
<lb/>matter and as you will
<lb/>see by an enclosure
<lb/>from him that is
<lb/>satisfactorily arranged
<lb/><unclear cert="low">pushed</unclear> a writing but
<lb/>they take care to do the
<lb/>opposite of what
<lb/><term type="occupation">lawyers</term> are liable too
<lb/>they are very chary of
<lb/>words on paper

	<pb facs="liv_001270_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>you need not return either
<lb/>of these. I am off on
<lb/><choice><sic>monday</sic><corr>Monday</corr></choice> <unclear cert="medium">forenoon</unclear>, the
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">Pearl</unclear> is out of dock
<lb/>with <unclear cert="low">merth</unclear> the Launch on
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">board</unclear>. It pleases us
<lb/>better than we expected</p>
<lb/><p>I <unclear cert="high">advised</unclear> John to
<lb/>make a <unclear cert="medium">destruction</unclear> between
<lb/>the men in power and
<lb/>the society itself - It is
<lb/>not unlikely but that
<lb/>after <unclear cert="low">Jenn</unclear> some they may
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">utter insimations against</unclear>

	<pb facs="liv_001270_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>I am not conscious of any one
<lb/>thing that can be brought up
<lb/>against me but should
<lb/>there be and especially in the
<lb/>"British Banner" which is
<lb/>in the hands of <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Tidman</persName> he
<lb/>should like to know of it
<lb/>and if you thought it <unclear cert="medium"><app><rdg cert="high">advisable</rdg><rdg>advisally</rdg></app></unclear> 
<lb/>would answer it. In the
<lb/>mean time I commit my 
	<lb/><unclear cert="medium">way</unclear> into the Lord &amp; trust he
<lb/>will guide me as he has
<lb/>done. I shall think over the
<lb/>matter of your notes</p>
<lb/><closer rend="indent">In the mean while
<lb/>may every blessing be on you &amp; yours
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>



            </div>
        </body>
    </text>

